content.description:
Climb the knobular 30-foot-tall pillar, step across, and finish to anchors for the route to the right (

Narrow Face

).  Beware of blocks that appear to be cemented but may break free. The climbing is decent, pro is fair, and rock is questionable (PG-13).

At the end, head to the anchor (

Deepwater Horizon

) on the right. This was bolted ground up on hooks. The crux is @ the 5th bolt.
